Mine is perl, for which the guts is<p><pre><code>    m/&quot;name&quot;:(&quot;.*?&quot;).*&quot;creditcard&quot;:(&quot;\d{4}(-\d{4}){3}&quot;)/ && print &quot;$1,$2\n&quot;
</code></pre>
i.e. if we we match what looks like a credit card in the credit card field then write the name and credit card.<p>The other only slightly tricky thing is the use of minimal match for the name field -- the ? after the *.
